PADDINGTON
BEAR
As described in Michael Bond's best-selling
book, ŌĆśA Bear Called PaddingtonŌĆÖ, Paddington
Bear first arrived at Paddington Station
in 1958.
Scenes from his first big-screen adventure
ŌĆśPaddingtonŌĆÖ, were filmed here at the station
in the autumn of 2013

[Bench]
PA(din)GTON STATION
Marmalade"Ķ
ÕDenis L. Begley
19th August 1953 - 20th February 2012
A tribute to a loving, thoughtful and caring man. Denis dedicated thirty-two years of his life to
nursing in the NHS and as a patient at the National, he appreciated sitting in this square.
He was dearly loved and his courage and determination will always be remembered.
Love always matey x x x x x"“
